... why would he?? If we agreed that you could have a shot at trak, why would we train you when you attempted him? We are perfectly capable of performing that corpse run ourselves, so it's not because we needed to &quot;sucker&quot; you into helping on the CR. It's also dumb to train him right before you were going to kill him. It would make more sense to train him on you when you were unbuffed and unorganized, to further ensure the failure of the raid. Second, just look at the facts. There are too many ways to aggro trak while pulling the mobs in his lair: bard songs, group buffing, shoddy pulling, etc. I myself have been on two different trak raids where he was aggro'd prematurely (but it was never my fault <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). Finally, how was he the ONLY person to survive?? If he aggro'd trakanon first, I would assume he would be the first to die. If he used DA to train you, you would have seen him run through your camp - did you? Before you jump to a conclusion, objectively look at the facts... in this case, I think Terhas recieves the &quot;reasonable doubt&quot; seal of approval. <p><html><b><green>Roliel Glorysong</b></green><i>World's worst tank,and a terrible singer too</i></html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urolielkotn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RolielKotN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/26/01 3:30:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=626.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Trak thing</span><hr size=1> Whoops, accidentally posted twice. <p><html><b><green>Roliel Glorysong</b></green><i>World's worst tank,and a terrible singer